law.text:
Every applicant for licensure as a landscape architect shall:
Be at least twenty-one (21) years of age;
Be a graduate of an accredited landscape architecture curriculum approved by the board;
Pass a national examination as prescribed by the board;
Submit a completed application as provided by the board through the promulgation of administrative regulations;
Pay the required fees; and
Document at least two (2) years of experience related to the practice of professional landscape architecture under the supervision of a licensed landscape architect, engineer, or architect, within five (5) years prior to submitting the application for licensure.
